article.headline: Wichita St. 67, Ill.-Chicago 60
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- P.J. Cousinard scored 15 points and Wichita State defeated Illinois-Chicago 67-60 on Monday in a consolation game at the Paradise Jam. Wichita State led by 13 points midway through the second half and held off a Flames rally that cut the lead to 63-60 with a minute to play. Gal Mekel went 4-for-4 from the free-throw line in the final seconds to secure the victory. Ramon Clemente had 10 points and 12 rebounds for the Shockers (2-2), who also got 10 points from Phillip Thomasson. Trailing 52-39 with 11:45 to play, Illinois-Chicago (2-3) went on a 10-2 run that included a 3-point play from Karl White. But the Flames, who trailed by just four at halftime, could never get closer than three points. White and Jeremy Buttell finished with 13 points each. Scott Vandermeer added 10 points and grabbed seven rebounds with five blocks. Wichita State shot 49 percent from the floor, while holding Illinois-Chicago to 39 percent.
